#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""worldmap — multi-layer real-time geo-intelligence console (terminal, Palantir-style).

Base : Natural Earth 1:110m coastlines (braille sub-pixel, dim brass) + an optional
       day/night terminator wash.
Live layers (free, NO API key), each toggleable, with pulsing markers + ping rings.
All glyphs are deliberately East-Asian-NARROW (eaw=N) so the fixed-width braille grid
never skews on terminals that render ambiguous-width chars as 2 cells:
  1 quakes     USGS all_day            ◉ / ✸  colored by magnitude
  2 news       GDELT GEO 2.0           ✚      geo-located world news (empty if unreachable)
  3 sat (ISS)  wheretheiss.at          ✦      live position + ground-track trail
  4 disasters  GDACS EVENTS4APP        ▴      cyclones/floods/quakes/volcano by alert level
  5 day/night  (astronomy, no network) ☼      night-side shading + subsolar point

Interaction:
  1..5 toggle layer       + / -  zoom        h j k l  pan        r  cycle region
  ↑↓←→ move cursor        Enter  pin/inspect nearest marker      Esc  unpin
  a    alerts on/off      L  legend          ?  help             q  quit

NETWORK / PRIVACY: read-only public GETs (USGS, GDELT, ISS, GDACS) — no personal data
leaves. WORLDMAP_OFFLINE=1 disables ALL network (coastlines + terminator still render).
Proximity ALERTS are the only outbound write: they send event text to YOUR OWN Telegram
via the repo's tools/telegram-send. OFF by default; toggle with `a` or
WORLDMAP_ALERTS=1. Deduped + rate-capped. Set home with WORLDMAP_HOME="lat,lon" (default 0,0).

Data: ~/.config/personal-ai/ne_110m_coastline.geojson (Natural Earth 1:110m, public domain)
"""
